━━━━━━━━━━
TECHNICAL DRAWINGS
━━━━━━━━━━

Placement:
- Bottom left and center

Style:
- Architectural line drawings
- Orthographic projection only

Views:
- Front view
- Side view
- Three-quarter cutaway or profile view

Line style:
- Fine technical lines
- Muted red or sepia tone
- Precise and restrained

Annotations:
- Measurement and construction callouts
- Neutral technical language
- Minimal density
- Editorial clarity over engineering clutter

STRICT RULE:
- NO perspective distortion in drawings

━━━━━━━━━━
MATERIALS PANEL
━━━━━━━━━━

Placement:
- Bottom right

Content:
- Material swatches (3–4 depending on product)

Format:
- Square or rectangular samples

Textures:
- Directly derived from the product materials
- Examples include:
  - fabric
  - leather
  - metal
  - wood
  - plastic

Labels:
- Small editorial captions
- Refined, technical tone
- No marketing language

